OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778371373
OL,3,CHungary's Peter Magyar sworn in as PM,
OL,4,Cending Viktor Orban's 16-year rule
OL,6,FHis government is expected to
OL,7,Ftransform political dynamics within
OL,8,Fthe European Union, where the former
OL,9,Fprime minister had upended the bloc by
OL,10,Ffrequently vetoing key decisions, most
OL,11,Frecently concerning support for
OL,12,Fneighbouring Ukraine.
OL,14,FOn Saturday, Magyar, a 45-year-old
OL,15,Flawyer who founded Tisza in 2024 after
OL,16,Fyears as an insider in Orban's party,
OL,17,Fentered the sprawling neo-Gothic
OL,18,Fparliament building alongside 140 of
OL,19,Fhis party representatives.
OL,26,@kD@LrrlD@RrpxD@[rp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
