OL,3,CHungary's Peter Magyar sworn in as PM,
OL,4,Cending Viktor Orban's 16-year rule
OL,6,FTisza now controls 141 seats in
OL,7,FHungary's 199-seat parliament. Orban's
OL,8,FFidesz-KDNP coalition controls 52
OL,9,Fseats, down from 135, while the far-
OL,10,Fright Mi Hazank (Our Homeland) party
OL,11,Fholds six seats.
OL,13,FThe 199 representatives took their
OL,14,Foaths of office at around 11 a.m.
OL,15,Flocal time. Orban was not among them
OL,16,Ffor the first time since Hungary's
OL,17,Ffirst post-Communist parliament was
OL,18,Fformed in 1990.
OL,26,@kD@LrrlD@RrpoD@crprD@MrpwD@Prp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
